      • search

        public java.util.List<Pair<java.lang.Integer,java.lang.Integer>> search(DensityGrid dg,
                                                                        Position startPos,
                                                                        Position endPos)
        Perform an astar search through the given DensitGrid, starting at startPos and ending at endPos. This assumes the grid has a set of static polygons Returns a list of grid coordinates defining a path, or null if no path found. This has the side effect of setting the searchedWeights values in the DensityGrid for display or analysis purposes.
        Specified by:
        search in interface DensityGridSearch
        Parameters:
        dg - density grid with polygon and initial weight information. Polygons must be static.
        startPos - Start position for search.
        endPos - Ending Position for search.
        Returns:

      • search

                                                                        Position startPos,
                                                                        Position endPos,
                                                                        double startTime,
                                                                        double gs)
        Perform a search on the given densitygrid, assuming a constant groundspeed. Polygons may be static or moving.
        Specified by:
        search in interface DensityGridTimedSearch
        Parameters:
        dg - Timed density grid with polygon and initial weight information. Polygons may be mosing or static.
        startPos - Start position for search.
        endPos - Ending Position for search.
        startTime - Absolute time to start the search at startPos
        gs - ground speed of aircraft
        Returns:
        List of grid coordinates for a successful path, or null if no path found.
